#MEM id=brand-analyst source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/prompt-systems/brand-analyst/SKILL.md savings=5%
M||tx|---
M||name|br-analyst
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Use this skill whenever the us provides a website URL and wants a br al, br DNA breakdown, visual identity audit, tone of voice study, or creative direction reference. Trigger when the us says things like "al this br", "give me a br breakdown", "what's the visual identity of", "al this website", "what's the br DNA", or "I need to understand how this br communicates". Also trigger when the us pastes a URL w/ creative or st intent. This skill produces a structured, art-director-grade br al covering positioning, visual language, photography direction, typography, color, and tone of voice — suitable as a creative brief reference or onboarding document for a new br project.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[an, data, kpi, cr, tn, mk-gap, ga4, pm]
M||tx|---
M|Bran|tx|Produce a precise, professional br DNA al from a website. Write as a senior art director or br strategist wld — no vague superlatives, no filler. Every observation must be specific, visual, and actionable.
M|Bran|tx|---
M|1. F|Use |
M|1. F|it|`/abt` or `/abt-us`
M|1. F|it|A pd or collection page
M|1. F|it|A cg or editorial page if detectable
M|1. F|Look|hero cp, pd descriptions, mission statements, visual styling cues described in CSS/class names, font references, im alt text, and any br voice in UI microcopy.
M|1. F|tx|Use `image_search` w/ the br name to pull visual references — pd shots, cg imagery, packaging — to inform the photography and visual tone section.
M|2. C|tx|Structure the output exactly as shown below. Do not add preamble or meta-commentary. Deliver the al directly.
M|2. C|tx|---
M|Outp|tx|Use this exact structure. Write in tight, declarative sentences. Avoid adjective stacks. Be precise.
M|Outp|tx|---
M|📷 B|tx|**br name**
M|📷 B|tx|**Sector / category**
M|📷 B|tx|**Founded / origin** *(if determinable)*
M|📷 B|tx|**br archetype** *(e.g. The Sage, The Creator, The Outlaw — use classic archetypes if applicable)*
M|📷 B|tx|**One-line br essence** *(what the br ultimately sells beyond the pd — e.g. "Permission to take up space" / "The quiet confidence of craft")*
M|📷 B|tx|---
M|🎯 P|tx|**Target audience**
M|🎯 P|Desc|demographics, psychographics, lifestyle markers, cultural references. Avoid generic descriptions like "millennials who care abt qual." Instead: "ds-literate urban professionals, 28–42, who read Kinfolk and buy Aesop. Distrust mass mk. Value provenance."
M|🎯 P|tx|**Competitive space**
M|🎯 P|tx|Where does it sit on the mk map? Premium / accessible / luxury / disruptive? Who are the implicit cr and how does this br differentiate?
M|🎯 P|tx|**br promise**
M|🎯 P|tx|The core value proposition, as the br implies it — not their tagline, but the underlying contract w/ the cs.
M|🎯 P|tx|**Cultural positioning**
M|🎯 P|tx|What world does this br inhabit? What references, movements, or aesthetics does it align w/ or borrow from?
M|🎯 P|tx|---
M|🎨 V|tx|**Primary palette**
M|🎨 V|tx|List colors w/ approximate hex values where determinable. Note dominant, secondary, and accent usage.
M|🎨 V|tx|**Typography**
M|🎨 V|Iden|hl font vs. body vs. UI. Note weight, tracking, and any distinctive typographic gestures (e.g., "all-caps lockups", "tight tracking on display tp", "humanist sans for approachability").
M|🎨 V|tx|**Logo & mark**
M|🎨 V|Desc|wordmark / lettermark / symbol. Note geometry, weight, any distinctive feature. What does the mark communicate abt the br's register?
M|🎨 V|tx|**Grid & layout language**
M|🎨 V|tx|How is space used? Generous white space / dense editorial / asymmetric / rigidly geometric? Any recurring compositional motifs?
M|🎨 V|tx|**Iconography & graphic devices**
M|🎨 V|Any |lines, shapes, textures, illustration style, pattern language.
M|🎨 V|tx|---
M|📷 P|tx|**Lighting style**
M|📷 P|Desc|natural diffused light / hard directional / studio flat / golden-hour warmth / hi-contrast chiaroscuro / clinical overexposed. Is shadow used or avoided?
M|📷 P|tx|**Colour grade**
M|📷 P|Desc|warm/cool, saturated/desaturated, lifted blacks, crushed highlights, matte finish, filmic grain. Reference a recognizable aesthetic if appropriate (e.g., "desaturated Scandinavian palette", "warm terracotta-shifted film tones").
M|📷 P|tx|**Typical composition**
M|📷 P|tx|How are subjects framed? Close crop / wide environmental / overhead flat-lay / editorial candid / formal symmetry? What's usually in frame?
M|📷 P|tx|**Surfaces, props, materials**
M|📷 P|tx|What textures and objects recur? (e.g., raw linen, poured concrete, glazed ceramic, unvarnished oak, worn leather) What materials are *never* used?
M|📷 P|tx|**md direction & casting**
M|📷 P|If p|how are they cast and directed? Expressive / neutral / candid / stylized / diverse / tp-cast? What does the casting say abt the br's world?
M|📷 P|tx|**Overall mood**
M|📷 P|tx|One to three sentences capturing the feeling of the visual world. What emotion does it elicit? What shd *not* be in this br's imagery?
M|📷 P|tx|---
M|✍️ T|tx|**Voice character**
M|✍️ T|Desc|"Speaks like a well-traveled architect who doesn't need to explain themselves" / "The confident older sister who gives direct advice w/o moralizing."
M|✍️ T|tx|**Writing style**
M|✍️ T|tx|Sentence length, rhythm, punctuation style, use of fragments. Does it use questions? Commands? Whisper or declare?
M|✍️ T|tx|**Key vocabulary**
M|✍️ T|tx|10–15 words or phrases that feel native to this br. These shd be words a copywriter wld reach for when writing in-br.
M|✍️ T|tx|**Vocabulary to avoid**
M|✍️ T|tx|8–12 words or phrases that wld feel instantly off-br. Include any overused category clichés this br deliberately sidesteps.
M|✍️ T|tx|**cn themes**
M|✍️ T|tx|What subjects does the br return to? What stories does it tell abt itself?
M|✍️ T|tx|**What the br never says**
M|✍️ T|tx|Describe the self-censorship at work — the register, topics, or attitudes the br wld never adopt.
M|✍️ T|tx|---
M|📋 C|tx|A closing paragraph (4–6 sentences) synthesizing the above into a working creative brief orientation. Written as if briefing a photographer, designer, or copywriter walking into their first day on this account. What is the single most important thing to understand abt this br's creative world?
M|📋 C|tx|---
M|Craf|it|If information is genuinely unavailable from the website, say "Not determinable from available cn" — do not fabricate.
M|Craf|- Wh|*(inferred)*.
M|Craf|it|Prioritize observed evidence over assumption. Ground every claim in something visible on the site.
M|Craf|- Us|colour theory, typographic terminology, photographic language, br st terms. This document shd be legible to a creative director.
M|Craf|- Av|"innovative," "cutting-edge," "passionate," "dedicated," "seamless," "world-class," "elevate," "journey." If the br uses these words, flag them as weaknesses in the tone of voice section.